  "detailed_description": "<p class=\"bb_paragraph\" >\"Improbability Control Bureau\" is a spot-the-difference horror game. Monitor live surveillance cameras. Spot anomalies. From eerie furniture shifts to unexpected intrusions, report anomalies to correct them and survive.</p><p class=\"bb_paragraph\" ></p><p class=\"bb_paragraph\" >As an agent of a classified organization, your mission is to monitor the live surveillance camera footage of locations reaching dangerously high levels of improbability and restore them to normality.</p><p class=\"bb_paragraph\" ></p><p class=\"bb_paragraph\" ><i>Note: There is only one level (with two slight variants) </i>  </p><p class=\"bb_paragraph\" ></p><h2 class=\"bb_tag\" >Shine your spotlight to report and disable anomalies</h2><p class=\"bb_paragraph\" ><span class=\"bb_img_ctn\"><video class=\"bb_img\" autoplay muted loop playsinline poster=\"https://shared.akamai.steamstatic.com/store_item_assets/steam/apps/2530060/extras/8d19d6b04e9fa01700d13967497948c7.poster.avif?t=1733782457\" width=594 height=334 ><source src=\"https://shared.akamai.steamstatic.com/store_item_assets/steam/apps/2530060/extras/8d19d6b04e9fa01700d13967497948c7.webm?t=1733782457\" type=\"video/webm; codecs=vp9\"><source src=\"https://shared.akamai.steamstatic.com/store_item_assets/steam/apps/2530060/extras/8d19d6b04e9fa01700d13967497948c7.mp4?t=1733782457\" type=\"video/mp4\"></video></span></p><p class=\"bb_paragraph\" >Survive the night and before all normality is lost forever!</p><p class=\"bb_paragraph\" ></p><p class=\"bb_paragraph\" >… Was that always there? </p><p class=\"bb_paragraph\" >Battle a growing sense of paranoia, armed only with your sharp eyes and memory.</p><p class=\"bb_paragraph\" ></p><p class=\"bb_paragraph\" ><span class=\"bb_img_ctn\"><video class=\"bb_img\" autoplay muted loop playsinline poster=\"https://shared.akamai.steamstatic.com/store_item_assets/steam/apps/2530060/extras/de14e107677644e98ded4b7dba67ca84.poster.avif?t=1733782457\" width=594 height=334 ><source src=\"https://shared.akamai.steamstatic.com/store_item_assets/steam/apps/2530060/extras/de14e107677644e98ded4b7dba67ca84.webm?t=1733782457\" type=\"video/webm; codecs=vp9\"><source src=\"https://shared.akamai.steamstatic.com/store_item_assets/steam/apps/2530060/extras/de14e107677644e98ded4b7dba67ca84.mp4?t=1733782457\" type=\"video/mp4\"></video></span></p><p class=\"bb_paragraph\" >The Improbability Control Bureau awaits! Are you prepared to safeguard normality in the face of improbability?</p><p class=\"bb_paragraph\" ></p><p class=\"bb_paragraph\" ><i>This game was made by a 2 person team: my girlfriend and I. She is responsible for most of the level design and overall art direction. While I have been primarily focused on developing the Improbability Engine that supports it. </i></p><p class=\"bb_paragraph\" ><i>Thank you for your continued support! </i></p><p class=\"bb_paragraph\" ></p><p class=\"bb_paragraph\" ><span class=\"bb_img_ctn\"><video class=\"bb_img\" autoplay muted loop playsinline poster=\"https://shared.akamai.steamstatic.com/store_item_assets/steam/apps/2530060/extras/cfc443672a54da67cc876c5096d11642.poster.avif?t=1733782457\" width=594 height=334 ><source src=\"https://shared.akamai.steamstatic.com/store_item_assets/steam/apps/2530060/extras/cfc443672a54da67cc876c5096d11642.webm?t=1733782457\" type=\"video/webm; codecs=vp9\"><source src=\"https://shared.akamai.steamstatic.com/store_item_assets/steam/apps/2530060/extras/cfc443672a54da67cc876c5096d11642.mp4?t=1733782457\" type=\"video/mp4\"></video></span></p><p class=\"bb_paragraph\" >Music by \"Karl Casey\" @ WhiteBatAudio</p>",
  "about_the_game": "<p class=\"bb_paragraph\" >\"Improbability Control Bureau\" is a spot-the-difference horror game. Monitor live surveillance cameras. Spot anomalies. From eerie furniture shifts to unexpected intrusions, report anomalies to correct them and survive.</p><p class=\"bb_paragraph\" ></p><p class=\"bb_paragraph\" >As an agent of a classified organization, your mission is to monitor the live surveillance camera footage of locations reaching dangerously high levels of improbability and restore them to normality.</p><p class=\"bb_paragraph\" ></p><p class=\"bb_paragraph\" ><i>Note: There is only one level (with two slight variants) </i>  </p><p class=\"bb_paragraph\" ></p><h2 class=\"bb_tag\" >Shine your spotlight to report and disable anomalies</h2><p class=\"bb_paragraph\" ><span class=\"bb_img_ctn\"><video class=\"bb_img\" autoplay muted loop playsinline poster=\"https://shared.akamai.steamstatic.com/store_item_assets/steam/apps/2530060/extras/8d19d6b04e9fa01700d13967497948c7.poster.avif?t=1733782457\" width=594 height=334 ><source src=\"https://shared.akamai.steamstatic.com/store_item_assets/steam/apps/2530060/extras/8d19d6b04e9fa01700d13967497948c7.webm?t=1733782457\" type=\"video/webm; codecs=vp9\"><source src=\"https://shared.akamai.steamstatic.com/store_item_assets/steam/apps/2530060/extras/8d19d6b04e9fa01700d13967497948c7.mp4?t=1733782457\" type=\"video/mp4\"></video></span></p><p class=\"bb_paragraph\" >Survive the night and before all normality is lost forever!</p><p class=\"bb_paragraph\" ></p><p class=\"bb_paragraph\" >… Was that always there? </p><p class=\"bb_paragraph\" >Battle a growing sense of paranoia, armed only with your sharp eyes and memory.</p><p class=\"bb_paragraph\" ></p><p class=\"bb_paragraph\" ><span class=\"bb_img_ctn\"><video class=\"bb_img\" autoplay muted loop playsinline poster=\"https://shared.akamai.steamstatic.com/store_item_assets/steam/apps/2530060/extras/de14e107677644e98ded4b7dba67ca84.poster.avif?t=1733782457\" width=594 height=334 ><source src=\"https://shared.akamai.steamstatic.com/store_item_assets/steam/apps/2530060/extras/de14e107677644e98ded4b7dba67ca84.webm?t=1733782457\" type=\"video/webm; codecs=vp9\"><source src=\"https://shared.akamai.steamstatic.com/store_item_assets/steam/apps/2530060/extras/de14e107677644e98ded4b7dba67ca84.mp4?t=1733782457\" type=\"video/mp4\"></video></span></p><p class=\"bb_paragraph\" >The Improbability Control Bureau awaits! Are you prepared to safeguard normality in the face of improbability?</p><p class=\"bb_paragraph\" ></p><p class=\"bb_paragraph\" ><i>This game was made by a 2 person team: my girlfriend and I. She is responsible for most of the level design and overall art direction. While I have been primarily focused on developing the Improbability Engine that supports it. </i></p><p class=\"bb_paragraph\" ><i>Thank you for your continued support! </i></p><p class=\"bb_paragraph\" ></p><p class=\"bb_paragraph\" ><span class=\"bb_img_ctn\"><video class=\"bb_img\" autoplay muted loop playsinline poster=\"https://shared.akamai.steamstatic.com/store_item_assets/steam/apps/2530060/extras/cfc443672a54da67cc876c5096d11642.poster.avif?t=1733782457\" width=594 height=334 ><source src=\"https://shared.akamai.steamstatic.com/store_item_assets/steam/apps/2530060/extras/cfc443672a54da67cc876c5096d11642.webm?t=1733782457\" type=\"video/webm; codecs=vp9\"><source src=\"https://shared.akamai.steamstatic.com/store_item_assets/steam/apps/2530060/extras/cfc443672a54da67cc876c5096d11642.mp4?t=1733782457\" type=\"video/mp4\"></video></span></p><p class=\"bb_paragraph\" >Music by \"Karl Casey\" @ WhiteBatAudio</p>",
